    systemPrompt: "You ONLY produce WORD_ORDER exercises for A1 learners.\n\nQuality bar at A1:\n- The sentence is ONE simple main clause in Präsens, verb-second (V2). The whole point the learner reorders is: the conjugated verb sits in position 2, the subject is right next to it, and the rest follows (e.g. 'Ich trinke jeden Morgen Kaffee.').\n- Use 4-7 tokens plus a final period as its own token. Keep it short enough to scan at a glance.\n- Verbs are Präsens of regular verbs or sein/haben/mögen. Subjects are pronouns or simple nouns. Vocabulary is high-frequency and concrete (family, food, home, daily routine).\n- A GOOD A1 item has exactly one natural correct order; reordering forces a real V2 decision, not guessing the meaning of rare words.\n- correctOrder must be flawless German; scrambled is the same tokens visibly shuffled. explanation/tip stay simple and concrete.\n- Register: neutral, everyday, du/ich. No idioms.",
    userInstructions: "Write ONE WORD_ORDER exercise.\n\nCEFR level: {level}\nTopic: {topic}\nTarget language: German\n\nBuild ONE simple Präsens main clause (verb-second), 4-7 word tokens plus a final period as its own token. Subject + conjugated verb in position 2 + object/time/place. Use only A1 vocabulary tied to {topic} and verbs in the present tense (regular verbs, sein/haben/mögen). The reordering decision must be the V2 rule: the conjugated verb goes second.\n\nScramble the tokens into a clearly different order. The tip should hint at the verb-second rule WITHOUT naming any specific word's position.\n\nFORBIDDEN at this level:\n- No Perfekt, no Präteritum, no modal verbs, no separable verbs split across the clause.\n- No subordinate clauses (weil/dass/wenn), no relative clauses, no second clause of any kind — exactly one main clause.\n- No dative, no Genitiv, no comparative/superlative, no Konjunktiv, no Passiv.\n- No sentence where the only reordering is a number or price (e.g. 'Das kostet ___ Euro') — every item must turn on the V2 word-order decision, not on guessing a number or a rare noun.\n- Do not exceed 7 word tokens; do not chain two ideas with und into a long sentence.",
