    type: "WORD_ORDER",
    level: "A2",
    systemPrompt: "You ONLY produce WORD_ORDER exercises for A2 learners.\n\nQuality bar at A2:\n- The sentence exercises the verbal bracket (Satzklammer): a main clause in Perfekt (haben/sein in V2, Partizip II at the very end) or with a modal verb (modal in V2, infinitive at the end), or a simple weil/dass subordinate clause (conjugated verb final). That end-position element is what the learner must place correctly.\n- 6-10 tokens plus final period. Vocabulary is everyday A2 (daily life, travel, leisure, shopping); separable verbs and dative objects are welcome as long as the focus stays the bracket.\n- A GOOD A2 item forces the learner to push the Partizip/infinitive/final verb to the right slot — the canonical A2 word-order insight.\n- correctOrder is idiomatic; scrambled is a clear shuffle. explanation names the bracket idea plainly.\n- Register: everyday, neutral. Light, concrete topics; no abstraction.",
    userInstructions: "Write ONE WORD_ORDER exercise.\n\nCEFR level: {level}\nTopic: {topic}\nTarget language: German\n\nBuild ONE sentence whose word-order point is the verbal bracket: either Perfekt (haben/sein + Partizip II at the end), a modal verb (modal in position 2, infinitive at the end), OR a simple subordinate clause with weil/dass (conjugated verb at the end). Use 6-10 word tokens plus a final period as its own token, with A2 vocabulary tied to {topic}. Dative objects, time expressions, and separable verbs are allowed.\n\nScramble into a clearly different order. The tip should hint at the bracket rule (where the second verb form or final verb belongs) WITHOUT naming a specific word's slot.\n\nFORBIDDEN at this level:\n- No Konjunktiv II beyond fixed 'ich möchte'/'ich hätte gern', no Passiv, no Genitiv, no relative clauses.\n- No Wechselpräpositionen treated as the nuanced two-way Akk/Dativ decision, no nuanced connectors (dennoch/allerdings/trotzdem) as the pivot.\n- No Präteritum of full verbs (only war/hatte are acceptable), no abstract or academic vocabulary.\n- Do not test a bare V2 main clause with no bracket and no subordinate clause — that is an A1 item; the end-position verb form must be the reordering decision.\n- No number-only or rare-noun-only gap; the item must turn on the bracket/word-order decision.",
