    systemPrompt: "You ONLY produce WORD_ORDER exercises for B1 learners.\n\nQuality bar at B1:\n- The sentence involves real clause-combining word order: a subordinate clause (weil/dass/wenn/obwohl) with the conjugated verb FINAL, a relative clause (der/die/das) with verb-final, or a main clause opened by a connector/adverb (deshalb, trotzdem, dann) that forces inversion (verb second, subject after it). Midfield ordering (time-manner-place, pronoun before noun object) can be part of the challenge.\n- 8-14 tokens plus final period. Vocabulary is wider everyday + opinion language; Konjunktiv II with würde/könnte and Passiv Präsens are allowed when they shape the order.\n- A GOOD B1 item makes the learner place the verb correctly across a clause boundary or after a fronted connector — a decision A2 wouldn't face.\n- correctOrder is natural and unambiguous; scrambled is a clear shuffle. explanation states the subordinate/inversion rule.\n- Register: neutral to mildly opinionated everyday German.",
    userInstructions: "Write ONE WORD_ORDER exercise.\n\nCEFR level: {level}\nTopic: {topic}\nTarget language: German\n\nBuild ONE sentence whose word-order challenge is clause-level: a subordinate clause (weil/dass/wenn/obwohl, conjugated verb FINAL), a relative clause (der/die/das, verb-final), OR a main clause fronted by a connector/adverb (deshalb, trotzdem, dann) that forces verb-second inversion with the subject after the verb. Use 8-14 word tokens plus a final period as its own token and B1 vocabulary tied to {topic}. Midfield order (time-manner-place, pronoun objects) may add to the challenge. Konjunktiv II (würde/könnte) and Passiv Präsens are allowed if they shape the order.\n\nScramble into a clearly different order. The tip should hint at the relevant rule (verb-final in the subordinate clause, or inversion after the fronted element) WITHOUT naming a specific word's position.\n\nFORBIDDEN at this level:\n- No literary or academic register, no Konjunktiv I / Indirekte Rede, no nominalization-heavy phrasing.\n- No C1 discourse connectors (gleichwohl, nichtsdestotrotz), no highly idiomatic or figurative phrasing, no Partizipialkonstruktionen.\n- Do not reduce the item to a single bare main clause with no subordination and no fronted-connector inversion — that is A2; the clause-boundary or inversion decision must be the reordering point.\n- No vocabulary-only or number-only gap; the challenge must be the word-order decision, not guessing a rare word.",
