    userInstructions: "Write ONE ERROR_CORRECTION exercise.\n\nCEFR level: {level}\nTopic: {topic}\nTarget language: German\n\nGuidance for this level:\n- Build a complex, multi-clause sentence on the topic above using a B2 structure: Konjunktiv I (Indirekte Rede), past/modal Konjunktiv II, Passiv in a non-present tense or with a modal, a Genitiv preposition (trotz/während/wegen), a prepositional or Genitiv relative clause, or a nuanced connector (dennoch/allerdings/hingegen/zumal).\n- Plant EXACTLY ONE error that is genuinely B2: wrong Konjunktiv I form in reported speech, a mis-formed past/modal Konjunktiv II or modal-Passiv, wrong case after a Genitiv preposition, a wrong Mittelfeld order, or a wrong preposition in a prepositional relative clause. Example seed: «*Trotz dem schlechten Wetter sind wir gewandert» → «Trotz des schlechten Wetters sind wir gewandert.»\n- errorDescription names the B2 fix precisely (e.g. «Genitiv nach «trotz»: «des … Wetters» statt «dem … Wetter».»). The tip nudges toward the subtle spot («Welchen Fall verlangt diese Präposition?») without giving the answer.\n\nFORBIDDEN at this level:\n- Do NOT dumb the item down to a single short main clause, an A1/A2-trivial gender/present-tense/simple-Perfekt slip, or any error a B1 learner would find unchallenging — the error must require B2 reasoning.\n- Do NOT avoid subordination: a flat SVO sentence with one easy error is not acceptable at this level.\n- Do NOT make the error a number, price, date, or unguessable vocabulary word with no grammatical decision behind it.\n- Do NOT pile on more than one error, and leave NO second accidental mistake in the carrier sentence.\n- Do NOT slip into ungrammatical over-formality or invented words while trying to raise difficulty.",
